Agency Name: Department of Health and Mental Hygiene
Resolution Description: The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene regulates restaurants and other establishments that mostly sell food which is prepared on the premises. New York State Agriculture and Markets regulates those establishments that mostly sell pre-packaged food, including supermarkets, bodegas, green markets, fish and meat markets, and delis. This Service Request involves an establishment under the jurisdiction of the New York State Agriculture and Markets. For complaint status, call (718) 722-2876.
